description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are a keen, enthusiastic individual with an excellent eye for detail and a positive approach, the Continuing Healthcare Team (CHC) would like to hear from you. An exciting opportunity has arisen for the post of Nurse Co-ordinator based in Worcestershire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The newly created Hereford and Worcester CCG (from 1 April) are looking for an individual who has excellent assessment skills and experience of working across a variety of care settings. The successful applicant will need to demonstrate enhanced communication skills and have the ability to work both as part of a team and autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of the FNC and CHC processes is preferred but not essential as we provide a three month induction and 12 month mentor to assist your transition to Continuing Healthcare. Alongside this the Team Leads and Clinical Lead aim to create a supportive and nurturing environment with a strong focus upon professional and personal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as assessing a patient’s eligibility of NHS Continuing Healthcare, the successful applicant will also manage a case load, support the appeals process and to work collaboratively with the team on any complaints or investigations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be a challenging and developing role that is varied and interesting and will need you to bring energy, flexibility and commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work is agile with flexibility to work from home where possible, the team are based at a brand new office at Acton house, Perdiswell Park, Worcester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to work flexibly across CCG offices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We invite you to call us or visit to discuss the role further please contact Victoria Owen 01905 681975&lt;/p&gt;
